This paper presents a path-planning approach for tethered robots. The proposed planner finds paths that minimize the tether tension due to tether–obstacle and tether–floor interaction.

[Download paper here](https://www.mdpi.com/2218-6581/14/2/11)

Recommended citation: <b>Lima, R. R.</b>, & Pereira, G. A. S. (2025). &quot; Tension-Aware Motion Planning for Tethered Robots &quot;. <i>Robotics</i>, 14(2), 11. https://doi.org/10.3390/robotics14020011
